{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"96bcb31a-c7ff-441c-964b-a934e9b67b72","content":"I don't have a specialized skill for **analyzing** crash dumps — the available `dump-collect` skill is only for *capturing* them.\n\nHere's how you can analyze your `.dmp` file:\n\n**Option 1: `dotnet-dump analyze`** (cross-platform)\n```bash\ndotnet tool install -g dotnet-dump   # if not already installed\ndotnet-dump analyze your-file.dmp\n```\nUseful SOS commands inside the session:\n- `clrstack` — managed call stack of the crashing thread\n- `pe` — print the last exception\n- `dumpheap -stat` — heap summary\n- `threads` — list all managed threads\n- `setthread <id>` + `clrstack` — inspect other threads\n\n**Option 2: WinDbg** (Windows, full native+managed)\n```\n.loadby sos coreclr\n!pe            // print exception\n!clrstack      // managed stack\n!threads       // all threads\n```\n\n**Option 3: Visual Studio**  \nOpen the `.dmp` → click **\"Debug with Managed Only\"** for an interactive debugging experience.\n\n---\n\nWould you like me to run `dotnet-dump analyze` on the file if you can provide its path? Or I can help you interpret output you paste here.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"1a047896-7a23-4892-b9f7-f071cf85eac1","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user has a .dmp crash dump file from a .NET application and wants help analyzing it to find the root cause of the crash. Let me look at the available skills to see if any are relevant.\n\nLooking at the available skills:\n- `dump-collect` - This is for *collecting* crash dumps, not analyzing them. The description explicitly says \"DO NOT USE FOR: analyzing or debugging dumps, post-mortem investigation with lldb/windbg/dotnet-dump analyze\"\n- `dotnet-trace-collect` - This is for capturing diagnostic artifacts, not analyzing dumps\n- `android-tombstone-symbolication` - For Android tombstones, not .dmp files\n\n\n- `apple-crash-symbolication` - For Apple .ips crash logs, not .dmp files\n\nNone of the available skills are designed for analyzing .dmp files, so I'll need to guide the user through the analysis process themselves using standard .NET debugging tools.","outputTokens":559,"requestId":"5018:2A473C:28D4C4:332BF1:69F555CB"},"id":"79710ad3-1caf-4998-b505-a5774def94a7","timestamp":"2026-05-02T01:39:37.003Z","parentId":"7c5d6157-76f0-4f2b-af84-6b8e74cbfbaa"}
